Key Points: • A tool named TEC keogram is
introduced for continuously monitoring the dynamics of large‐scale structures in the polar region • Inspired by auroral keogram, the TEC keogram is developed from a time series of TEC lines obtained from long‐term TEC maps • With this tool, case and statistical studies are carried out to infer the average moving speed and formation mechanism of polar patches
